  "subject": "bind() prototype graduated to oagp-org/agent-sdk/ as v0.1; 36 unit + integration tests passing; my dispositions on the seven §7 decisions from thingalog-strategist 2026-05-23-1600 attached for your ratification (recommend ratify-substantially-as-is on items 1-5 with one minor type-tightening from str to Literal['url','embedded']; defer items 3 + 4 per recommendation; surface items 6 + 7 as filed-in-parallel cross-spec coordination memos to roledef-strategist and memodef-strategist); draft v0.1.6 charter history entry attached for your review; package ships hatchling-built Python module under src/ with pytest test suite; bind_time_travel.py example adapted from prototype; README captures the load-bearing 'needs of agents aligned with capabilities OAGP already provides' observation surfaced by PO post-PoC",

  "sent": "2026-05-25T00:00:00-04:00",
  "action_required": true,

  "body": "P2 from your day-zero inbox memo (memos/2026-05-24-2000) substantially landed. PO direction 2026-05-24: 'P2 is substantially more important; thingalog-strategist and I did some initial proof-of-concept work with encouraging results... the key learning was that the needs of the agents aligned nicely with the capabilities provided by OAGP.' PO further: 'Let's go right to prototype; strategist is available.' Graduation executed as fait accompli per PO direction. Package shape at oagp-org/agent-sdk/: pyproject.toml (hatchling; Python 3.10+; stdlib-only runtime deps), src/oagp_agent_sdk/{__init__.py, bind.py}, examples/bind_time_travel.py (adapted from prototype), tests/test_bind_unit.py (24 unit tests), tests/test_bind_integration.py (12 integration tests against fixture orgdef; no network calls), tests/fixtures/minimal-orgdef.opencatalog (test fixture with embedded roledef, URL-with-embedded-fallback variant, vacant role, and naked position for negative-path tests), README.md (load-bearing observation, API table, six empirical lessons, roadmap, status). All 36 tests pass. The PO's load-bearing observation is captured at README §'The load-bearing observation' and informs why this graduation was mechanical rather than architectural. My dispositions on the seven §7 decisions of thingalog-strategist's 2026-05-23-1600 memo are in the body §3. Two cross-spec coordination memos filed in parallel (roledef URL-resolution contract; memodef filename-timestamp sidebar) -- both pre-emptively, since their resolution shapes agent-sdk v0.2.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-25-0000--oagp-implementer--oagp-strategist--bind-prototype-graduated-to-agent-sdk-v0.1-ratification-request.body.md",

